# WellnessHub ‚Äì Fully Styled, Plug-and-Play HTML

This project is a complete, responsive, and accessible **WellnessHub** landing page with dark mode, mobile navigation, testimonial slider, search functionality, and a modal popup for starting your journey.


## Features
- üåó **Dark Mode Toggle** with smooth transitions
- üì± **Mobile Navigation Menu**
- üîç **Search Filtering** for blog posts/services
- üí¨ **Testimonial Slider**
- üìç **Contact Section** with embedded Google Map
- üìù **Modal Form** for ‚ÄúStart Your Journey‚Äù CTA
- ‚ö° Fully responsive and accessible

## Database Design
While this HTML template is front-end only, here‚Äôs a suggested relational database schema if you integrate it with a backend:
```
Users
- id (PK)
- name
- email
- password_hash
- created_at

BlogPosts
- id (PK)
- title
- content
- author_id (FK -> Users.id)
- created_at

Services
- id (PK)
- name
- description
- price
- created_at

Testimonials
- id (PK)
- user_id (FK -> Users.id)
- content
- rating
- created_at
```

## Technology Stack (Suggested)
- **Frontend:** HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript 
- **Icons:** Font Awesome
- **Fonts:** Google Fonts ‚Äì Poppins
- **Backend (Optional):** Laravel / Node.js + Express
- **Database (Optional):** MySQL / MongoDB
- **Hosting:** Netlify / Vercel / cPanel Hosting /github

## UI Screenshots (Descriptions)
1. **Hero Section:** A full-width background image with a centered heading, short tagline, and the ‚ÄúStart Your Journey‚Äù button.
2. **Services Grid:** Three neatly aligned cards, each with a colored icon at the top, a bold service title, and short description text.
3. **Testimonials Slider:** Horizontal carousel of client feedback with profile images, names, star ratings, and their written testimonials.
4. **Blog Section:** Grid layout of blog article cards with featured images, titles, and preview text, alongside a search bar at the top.
5. **Contact Form:** Clean two-column section with a contact form on one side and an embedded Google Map on the other.
6. **Dark Mode Preview:** Shows the entire UI in dark mode with smooth transitions and readable contrast.

*(Screenshots to be added when deployed)*

